# Review & commit standards

> **Compliance:** Part of mandatory agent rules (`agents-mandatory.mdc`). Apply on every implementation, review, commit, and PR.

Apply on every implementation task, code review, and when the user asks for a commit or PR.

## Before claiming done (self-review)

1. **Scope** ‚Äî Smallest correct diff; no drive-by refactors or unrelated files.
2. **Architecture** ‚Äî Domain ‚Üê data ‚Üê presentation; screen models do not import `*Impl`.
3. **i18n** ‚Äî New UI copy in all 8 `values*` locales; composables use `stringResource`; screen models expose data, not formatted English.
4. **Design system** ‚Äî Reuse `Journey*` / `FamilyLogistics*` / `JourneySemanticColors`; no raw `OutlinedTextField`, `Icons.Default`, or one-off hex colors.
5. **UX states** ‚Äî Loading, error, empty handled; snackbars above `bottomBar` where applicable; `imePadding` on text-heavy screens.
6. **Tests ‚Äî new coverage** ‚Äî Every new domain method, screen model transition, codec, and composable screen has a unit or instrumented test. New `LazyColumn`/`LazyRow` `items()` blocks use stable, prefixed keys. New screens have `*TestTags` constants.
7. **Tests ‚Äî existing coverage updated** ‚Äî Every modified function whose behavior changed has its test updated to match. No stale `assertEquals`/`assert` that passes for the wrong reason. Fakes implement the full current interface with no `TODO()` stubs.
8. **QA YAML** ‚Äî Update `firebase-appdistribution-testcases.yaml` (bump `version`) when user-facing flows change.
9. **Secrets** ‚Äî No credentials, `local.properties` values, or `google-services.json` in commits.
10. **Gradle** ‚Äî Run `:composeApp:testDebugUnitTest` (must be `BUILD SUCCESSFUL`) and `:composeApp:compileDebugAndroidTestKotlinAndroid` (must compile clean) before done.

## PR checklist

- Title: imperative, feature-focused (match repo style).
- Body: summary bullets + test plan (unit / instrumented / manual).
- CI: `gh pr checks N --watch` until green before merge.
- Merge: squash to `main`; delete feature branch.
- Release: **manual only** ‚Äî `gh workflow run "KMP CI" --ref main -f job=release -f version_bump=patch` (not on every PR).

## Commit rules

- Commit **only when the user explicitly asks** (or clearly requests ‚Äúship‚Äù / ‚Äúcommit‚Äù / ‚Äúfinish with release‚Äù).
- Message: 1‚Äì2 sentences, **why** not just what; use HEREDOC for formatting.
- Never: `--no-verify`, force-push to `main`, amend unless user requested and HEAD is unpushed local commit.
- Pre-commit: `git status`, `git diff`, `git log -1` for style; exclude secret files.

## Review feedback priorities (blockers first)

| Priority | Check |
|----------|--------|
| P0 | Security (RLS, auth, secrets), data loss, crash |
| P1 | i18n parity, viewer read-only violations, wrong layer imports, **unit test compile failure or `BUILD FAILED`** |
| P2 | **Missing tests for new code**, **stale tests not updated for changed behavior**, **fakes out of sync with interface**, broken `testTag`s, Firebase YAML drift |
| P3 | Design-system drift (non-Journey controls), touch targets &lt; 48dp |
| P4 | Naming, minor style |

## Anti-patterns in review

- Hardcoded English in Kotlin UI layers.
- `stringResource` inside `LaunchedEffect` / non-`@Composable` lambdas.
- Business logic in `@Composable` bodies.
- Mixing AI read-only lists with editable CRUD without explicit UX separation.
- Phone-only layout assumptions (test wide ‚â• `ScreenLayout.expandedMinWidth` when touching grocery/meal plan).
- **New public methods/classes with no test** ‚Äî every shipped function is a contract; untested contracts break silently.
- **Tests that were not updated after a behavior change** ‚Äî a test that passes despite the implementation changing is a false green; it hides future regressions.
- **Fake left with `TODO()` or incomplete interface** ‚Äî downstream tests silently skip untested paths; treat as a crash equivalent.
- **`LazyColumn`/`LazyRow` items keyed by display text or non-unique property** ‚Äî causes `IllegalArgumentException` at runtime; use stable IDs with type prefixes when multiple `items()` blocks share a column.
